SIMPLE: sanctify
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sanctify
<hw>Sanc"ti*fy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Sanctified</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Sanctifying</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>sanctifier</ets>, L. <ets>sanctificare</ets>; <ets>sanctus</ets>
holy + <ets>-ficare</ets> (in comp.) to make. See <er>Saint</er>, and
<er>-fy</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To make sacred or holy; to set
apart to a holy or religious use; to consecrate by appropriate rites; to
hallow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>God blessed the seventh day and <qex>sanctified</qex> it.</q>
<rj><qau>Gen. ii. 3.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Moses . . . <qex>sanctified</qex> Aaron and his garments.</q>
<rj><qau>Lev. viii. 30.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To make free from sin; to cleanse from moral
corruption and pollution; to purify.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Sanctify</qex> them through thy truth.</q> <rj><qau>John
xvii. 17.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To make efficient as the means of holiness; to
render productive of holiness or piety.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A means which his mercy hath <qex>sanctified</qex> so to me as to
make me repent of that unjust act.</q> <rj><qau>Eikon
Basilike.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To impart or impute sacredness, venerableness,
inviolability, title to reverence and respect, or the like, to; to
secure from violation; to give sanction to.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The holy man, amazed at what he saw,⟦br⟧
Made haste to <qex>sanctify</qex> the bliss by law.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Truth guards the poet, <qex>sanctifies</qex> the line.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sanctifyingly</ent>⟦br⟧
